00:50:14,470 --> 00:50:17,974
- So what am I thinking?
- My guess...

705
00:50:18,057 --> 00:50:22,103
You witnessed a waste of time,
money, energy and, in a few cases, talent.

706
00:50:22,854 --> 00:50:28,359
Rawls says it's burrell's numbers game. Says
if I unleash him, all that bullshit goes south.

707
00:50:28,443 --> 00:50:33,114
A return of high-end police work
and it'll be the dawning of a new day.

708
00:50:33,323 --> 00:50:35,867
- Rawls said that?
- Yeah.

709
00:50:35,950 --> 00:50:40,288
Says he's just following orders,
being a good soldier.

710
00:50:40,371 --> 00:50:42,415
What do you say?

711
00:50:43,541 --> 00:50:48,296
Mr. Mayor, if you want to talk about what
happens in the street or in the western,

712
00:50:48,379 --> 00:50:52,592
I'll talk your ear off.
But I'm a soldier too.

713
00:50:52,675 --> 00:50:54,886
I don't go up the chain with my opinions.

714
00:50:54,969 --> 00:50:56,721
I can respect that.

715
00:50:56,804 --> 00:51:01,059
I will say this though -
we did have one unit doing high-end stuff,

716
00:51:01,142 --> 00:51:04,687
major crimes working out
of an offsite on Clinton street.

717
00:51:04,771 --> 00:51:07,982
"Did" is past tense. What wrecked it?

718
00:51:10,151 --> 00:51:12,737
Good question, Mr. Mayor.

719
00:51:12,820 --> 00:51:16,950
With ray foerster's passing, I need
a new cid commander right away.

720
00:51:17,033 --> 00:51:20,411
Would you object to being
a colonel working under rawls?

721
00:51:24,666 --> 00:51:27,835
- Under rawls?
- He is deputy ops, is he not?

722
00:51:30,004 --> 00:51:33,675
Will the mayor make the changes
or leave it to the good soldier?

723
00:51:35,677 --> 00:51:39,097
What I'm really asking is -
how for real are you?

724
00:51:40,098 --> 00:51:44,435
Well, I guess we're going to
find that out together, aren't we...

725
00:51:44,519 --> 00:51:46,187
Colonel Daniels?

726
00:51:51,734 --> 00:51:53,736
What the fuck do we do?

727
00:51:55,029 --> 00:51:58,533
- I don't know.
- These guys don't scare.

728
00:52:00,410 --> 00:52:03,454
If we all kick in, you, me, sydnor,

729
00:52:03,538 --> 00:52:05,581
maybe we could afford a used camera?

730
00:52:05,665 --> 00:52:10,837
I thought of that. It ain't gonna match
the serial numbers from the one from isd.

731
00:52:15,091 --> 00:52:18,970
We've gotta get wood on marlo.
It's the only way.

732
00:52:20,221 --> 00:52:23,391
This Randy kid,
he can't give us a murder, right?

733
00:52:23,474 --> 00:52:25,977
Shit, he can't even give us a body.

734
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:27,979
But he says some little Kevin kid

735
00:52:28,062 --> 00:52:32,150
was the one supposed
to tell Lex to go up in that alley.

736
00:52:32,233 --> 00:52:34,944
Plus, what did fucknut say little kev said?

737
00:52:36,112 --> 00:52:39,240
"Lex went up the alley
but he ain't coming back."

738
00:52:40,116 --> 00:52:44,203
Maybe he saw the whole thing.
Maybe he's our eyeball witness.

739
00:52:44,746 --> 00:52:46,748
- Little Kevin.
- Little Kevin.

740
00:52:58,051 --> 00:53:01,846
80, 100, 10, 20.420.

741
00:53:01,929 --> 00:53:03,931
Where's the rest?

742
00:53:05,099 --> 00:53:08,728
Um, I'm on a hard strip.
It's tricky on Lafayette.

743
00:53:08,811 --> 00:53:11,898
- What the fuck are you doing there?
- I gotta build it up.

744
00:53:11,981 --> 00:53:15,777
No, no, you ain't got to build up shit.
Your father built them corners

745
00:53:15,860 --> 00:53:18,613
and they owe you cos they owe him.

746
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:22,867
Bodie got a real short memory
when it comes to giving props. Hm.

747
00:53:28,748 --> 00:53:30,917
I'm going to straighten
this shit out right now.

748
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:32,502
Ma, let me build.

749
00:53:38,466 --> 00:53:40,176
Sir.

750
00:53:40,259 --> 00:53:41,928
Bill...

751
00:53:44,931 --> 00:53:47,225
We need to regroup.

752
00:53:47,308 --> 00:53:51,479
Come up with something fresh
for the new administration.

753
00:53:55,691 --> 00:53:57,568
I don't mind telling you,

754
00:53:57,652 --> 00:54:01,614
I'm uncomfortable with the way
carcetti is running around in our shop...

755
00:54:01,697 --> 00:54:05,159
He's talked to me, several times.

756
00:54:08,830 --> 00:54:10,498
Huh.

757
00:54:11,457 --> 00:54:13,292
You're making your move, huh?

758
00:54:21,968 --> 00:54:24,846
We were a good team, you and me.

759
00:54:26,514 --> 00:54:28,683
We were.

760
00:54:56,461 --> 00:54:59,714
- Miss Ella, where bug at?
- He went home, Michael.

761
00:54:59,797 --> 00:55:01,549
Nah, he waits for me.

762
00:55:01,632 --> 00:55:04,635
The man who picked him up
said he was his father.

763
00:55:04,719 --> 00:55:06,929
And bug said so, too.

764
00:55:07,013 --> 00:55:08,848
Fuck!

765
00:55:09,849 --> 00:55:11,934
Mm.

766
00:55:31,579 --> 00:55:33,915
What the fuck did you do?

767
00:55:34,957 --> 00:55:37,251
- And why'd you let him do it?
- Listen...

768
00:55:37,335 --> 00:55:42,840
No. That's how you got him with his head up
his ass, unsolving his own fucking murders.

769
00:55:43,508 --> 00:55:46,552
Your job is to turn red to black,
not the other way.

770
00:55:47,762 --> 00:55:50,932
And you, stand the fuck up for yourself.

771
00:56:00,441 --> 00:56:05,488
You don't gotta do the whole thing on your
fingers, little man. Look, first column.

772
00:56:05,571 --> 00:56:08,574
- Six and six is...
- 12.

773
00:56:08,658 --> 00:56:11,452
Put down the two, you bring over the one.

774
00:56:11,536 --> 00:56:13,496
- Bug.
- Hey, big man.

775
00:56:13,579 --> 00:56:15,581
- Get over to me now.
- We were going...

776
00:56:15,665 --> 00:56:17,583
Now.

777
00:56:47,989 --> 00:56:49,991
Yo, hold on.

778
00:57:18,102 --> 00:57:21,397
Yo, you owe me 800 on that, bitch. You owe.

